# Tank Wars — Project Guidelines

This is a hobby / learning project.

## Code changes

- Only add or modify code when the user specifically asks for it.
- Otherwise, suggest solutions in chat rather than implementing them.

## Learning-first responses

- When the user asks for information, give hints that help them find the answer themselves.
- Prefer guiding questions and pointers over direct answers.

## Architecture documentation

- Project architecture documentation lives in `doc/arc42`, following the [arc42](https://arc42.org) template.
- Start at `doc/arc42/README.md` for the chapter index (introduction, building blocks, ADRs, technical debt, etc.).
- When documenting or looking up architectural decisions, constraints, or system design, use the relevant arc42 chapter rather than inventing a new location.


## Ticket Documentation
 - Backlog of tickets is in doc\v1\roadmap.md